cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper presents a novel design methodology for architecting a DNN architecture for vision applications, specifically for color constancy. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes an implicit regularization technique, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the efficiency of the proposed architecture, which could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper demonstrates the effectiveness of the proposed architecture on imaging pipelines, which could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia).
